[Sarah G. Live| Sarah G. Live!]]''\n| Host/Performer\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[The Voice of the Philippines]] [[The Voice of the Philippines (season 1)|(season 1)]]''\n| rowspan=\"7\" |Coach\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[The Voice Kids (Philippine TV series)|The Voice Kids]] [[The Voice Kids (Philippines season 1)|(season 1)]]''\n|-\n| 2014\u20132015\n| ''[[The Voice of the Philippines]] [[The Voice of the Philippines (season 2)|(season 2)]]''\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[The Voice Kids (Philippine TV series)|The Voice Kids]] [[The Voice Kids (Philippines season 2)|(season 2)]]''\n|-\n| 2017\n| ''[[The Voice Teens (Philippine TV series)|The Voice Teens]] [[The Voice Teens (Philippines season 1)|(season 1)]]''\n|-\n| 2019\n| ''[[The Voice Kids (Philippine TV series)|The Voice Kids]] [[The Voice Kids (Philippines season 4)|(season 4)]]''\n|-\n| 2020\n| ''[[The Voice Teens (Philippine TV series)|The Voice Teens]] [[The Voice Teens (Philippine season 2)|(season 2)]]''\n|}\n\n==Awards and accolades==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Sarah Geronimo}}\nSarah Geronimo has received more than 200 awards in the entertainment industry (music, film, and television) and from other organizations including different international award-giving bodies including 12 [[Awit Award]]s, 8 [[Aliw Award]]s, 28 [[Myx Music Award]]s (the most in the awards history) and a [[FAMAS Award|FAMAS Golden Artist Award]]. She has also won the [[2012 Mnet Asian Music Awards|Best Asian Artist]] at the [[Mnet Asian Music Awards]]<nowiki/>in 2012, [[MTV Europe Music Award for Best Southeast Asian Act|Best Southeast Asian Act]] at the [[MTV Europe Music Awards]] in 2014, Best Selling Filipino Artist at the [[2014 World Music Awards|22nd World Music Awards]] and Best Asian Performer at [[Classic Rock Roll of Honour Awards]] in 2016. She was inducted into the Anak TV Hall of Fame in 2013. Geronimo is a Goodwill Ambassador for Music of the [[National Commission for Culture and the Arts]] and a recipient of their [[Ani ng Dangal]] or \"Harvest of Honors\" state recognition for multi-disciplinary arts.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<!-- <ref name=\"Sarah Geronimo's Early works\">{{cite news|last = Samio|first = Veronica R.|title = May pang tuition na si Sarah! (Sarah Geronimo's Early life)|publisher = philstar.com|date = August 27, 2003|url = http://www.philstar.com/Article.aspx?articleId=218774&publicationSubCategoryId=96|accessdate = January 25, 2010}}</ref> -->\n\n<ref name=\"Sarah Geronimo in Platinum Circle Awards1\">{{cite news|last = Smith|first = Chuck|title = Platinum Circle Awards1|publisher = Pep.ph|date = December 22, 2008|url = http://www.pep.ph/guide/3122/Pinoy-singers-join-the-Platinum-Circle|accessdate = January 25, 2010}}</ref>\n\n<!-- <ref name=\"abante1\">{{cite news|last = Garcia|first = Rose|title = Sarah emotional in Araneta|publisher = abante.com.ph|date = November 7, 2009|url = http://www.abante.com.ph/issue/nov0909/ent_other04.htm|accessdate = January 25, 2010}}</ref> -->\n\n<ref name=\"inquirer1\">{{cite news|title = Big Dome Triumph|publisher = inquirer.net|date = November 11, 2009|url = http://services.inquirer.net/print/print.php?article_id=20091111-235638|accessdate = January 25, 2010}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"manila standard1\">{{cite news|last = Red|first = Isah V.|title = Sarah Geronimo on a path to superstardom|publisher = manilastandardtoday.com|date = August 22, 2007|url = http://www.manilastandardtoday.com/2007/aug/22/goodLife3.htm|archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110714050026/http://www.manilastandardtoday.com/2007/aug/22/goodLife3.htm|archivedate = July 14, 2011|accessdate = January 25, 2010}}</ref>\n\n<!-- <ref name=\"Sarah Geronimo as Regine's Heir\">{{cite news|last = Lo|first = Richardo F.|title = Sarah: Regine\u2019s heiress apparent|publisher = philstar.com|date = October 3, 2003|url = http://www.philstar.com/funfare/article.aspx?articleid=222856&publicationsubcategoryid=70|accessdate = January 25, 2010}}</ref> -->\n\n<!-- <r