{"title_page": "Second Sino-Japanese War", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2013}}\n{{Infobox military conflict\n| conflict = Second Sino-Japanese War\n| partof = [[Interwar Period]] and the [[Pacific War|Pacific Theater]] of [[World War II]]{{efn|From 1941 onward|group=efn}}\n| image = Second Sino-Japanese War collection.png\n| image_size = 300px\n| caption = '''Clockwise from top left''': The Imperial Japanese Navy (IJN) Special Naval Landing Forces troops in gas masks prepare for an [[Battle of Shanghai|advance in the rubble of Shanghai]], 1944 [[Operation Ichigo]] IJA Type 92 Heavy machine gun, dead victims of the [[Nanjing Massacre]] on the shore of the [[Qinhuai River]] with a Japanese soldier standing nearby, Chinese machine gun nest in the [[Battle of Wuhan]], Japanese [[Bombing of Chongqing]], [[X Force|the Chinese Expeditionary Force]] in India in 1942\n| date = July 7, 1937 \u2013 September 2, 1945<br /><small>Minor fighting since [[Mukden Incident|September 18, 1931]]</small><br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=07|day1=07|year1=1937|month2=09|day2=02|year2=1945}})\n| place = [[Mainland China]] and [[British rule in Burma|Burma]]\n| territory = [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|China]] recovers all territories lost to [[Empire of Japan|Japan]] since the [[Treaty of Shimonoseki]], but [[Mongolian People's Republic#1945 Sino-Soviet Treaty and Mongolia's independence|loses Outer Mongolia]].\n| result = Chinese victory as part of the [[Allies of World War II|Allied]] victory in the [[Pacific War]]\n* Surrender of Japanese forces in mainland China (excluding [[Manchuria]]), [[Taiwan]], the [[Spratly Islands]], the [[Paracel Islands]], and [[French Indochina]] north of [[16th parallel north|16\u00b0 north]] to the [[Republic of China (1912\u20131949)|Republic of China]] after losing territory to China\n* China as one of the [[Four Policemen|Big Four of the Allies]] becomes permanent member of the [[United Nations Security Council|UN Security Council]]\n* Resumption of the [[Chinese Civil War]]\n| combatant1 = {{plainlist|\n* '''{{flagcountry|Republic of China (1912\u201349)}}'''<br />{{small|([[Nationalist Government]] led a Chinese [[Second United Front|united front]] which included [[Kuomintang|Nationalists]], [[Communist Party of China|Communists]], and [[Warlord era|regional warlords]].)}}\n* ''Foreign support'':\n** {{flag|Soviet Union|1936}}<br /><small>(1937\u201341, 1944\u201345)</small>\n** {{flag|United States|1912}}<br /><small>(1941\u201345)</small>\n** {{flag|British Empire}}<br /><small>(1942\u201345)</small>}}\n| combatant2 = {{plainlist|\n* '''{{flagcountry|Empire of Japan}}'''\n* ''[[Collaborationist Chinese Army|Collaborator support]]'':\n** {{flagicon image|Flag of the Republic of China-Nanjing (Peace, National Construction).svg|size=23px}} [[Wang Jingwei regime|Reorganized National Government]] <small>(1940\u201345)</small>\n** {{flag|Manchukuo|size=23px}} <small>(1932\u201345)</small>\n** {{flag|Mengjiang|size=23px}} <small>(1936\u201345)</small>\n** {{nowrap|{{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|1912|size=23px}} [[Provisional Government of the Republic of China (1937\u20131940)|Provisional Government]]}}<br /><small>(1937\u201340)</small>\n** {{nowrap|{{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|1912|size=23px}} [[Reformed Government of the Republic of China|Reformed Government]]}}<br /><small>(1938\u201340)</small>\n** {{nowrap|{{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|1912|size=23px}} [[East Hebei Autonomous Government|East Hebei]]}}<br /><small>(1935\u201338)</small>\n}}\n| commander1 = {{plainlist|\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|size=30px}} '''[[Chiang Kai-shek]]'''\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[He Yingqin]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[Chen Cheng]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[Tang Shengzhi]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[Cheng Qian]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[Bai Chongxi]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[Li Zongren]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[Wei Lihuang]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[Yan Xishan]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[Xue Yue]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[Gu Zhutong]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[Fu Zuoyi]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[Zhang Fakui]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{Flagicon image|Naval Jack of the Republic of China.svg|size=21px}} [[Sun Lianzhong]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{flagicon image|Flag of the Chinese Communist Party (Pre-1996).svg|size=21px}} [[Mao Zedong]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201349)|army|size=23px}} {{flagicon image|Flag of the Chinese Communist Party (Pre-1996).svg|size=21px}} [[Zhu De]]\n* {{Flagdeco|Republic of China (1912\u201